I.u[11306] = {n:"Efferves Sword",t:6,d:"Engraved on its handle you can read: \"This sword steals the life of the poor and redistributes it to the rich.\" Too bad you\'re poor.",ep:0,g:0,l:49,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,e:[5,5,1,1,45,50,false,false],p:4900};
I.u[11307] = {n:"Az le Tech\'s Cursed Treasure",t:94,d:"Az le Tech wanted to trade this treasure for his freedom with the Enutrof conqueror Sétroc. Once in his possession, Sétroc did not keep his word and executed Az le Tech. As he lay dying, he cast a curse that will befall anyone who lays their hands on this treasure.",ep:0,g:0,l:1,wd:false,fm:true,w:1,an:0,u:true,p:1};
I.u[11308] = {n:"Az le Tech\'s Curse",t:30,d:"You have stolen some of Az le Tech\'s treasure. Look what happens to greedy people.",ep:0,g:0,l:1,wd:false,fm:true,w:0,an:0,m:true,p:1};
I.u[11309] = {n:"Talklyka Pirate Claw",t:47,d:"Very handy for pinching the buttocks of its enemies or grabbing pickles stuck to the bottom of the jar, this claw is a Talklyka Pirate\'s pride and joy.",ep:0,g:0,l:145,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11310] = {n:"Talklyka Pirate Rope",t:15,d:"It\'s difficult to say what purpose this rope could serve for a Talklyka Pirate, because everyone knows they haven\'t got a clue how to tie knots.",ep:0,g:0,l:145,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11311] = {n:"Karrybean Pirate Buoy",t:15,d:"Some pirates can\'t swim and so they need a buoy. They may eventually beach on the black sand beaches of the Cradle of Alma after floating around for several years. Once they\'ve back on terra firma, they\'re generally thirsty for revenge. But since they can\'t take revenge on the sea, they take revenge on the weak, as well as tourists, or just simply weak tourists.",ep:0,g:0,l:145,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11312] = {n:"Karrybean Pirate Tail",t:65,d:"It\'s difficult to call this a tail, it\'s more of a Karrybean Pirate extremity.",ep:0,g:0,l:145,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11313] = {n:"Yuara Pirate Oil",t:60,d:"Yuara Pirates always keep a little oil with them to ensure that their wheel rotates correctly, but end up drinking it in a misguided attempt to stop their heads rotating instead.",ep:0,g:0,l:150,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11314] = {n:"Yuara Pirate Shell",t:111,d:"This shell protected the Yuara Pirate from sea spray and guano while it was sailing. Now it\'s beached, it uses it to protect its delicate pupils from the black sandstorms of the Cradle of Alma.",ep:0,g:0,l:150,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11315] = {n:"Retspan Pirate Mast",t:38,d:"Ignorant people might think this is a Spinnaker pole or a bowsprit, while any Frigostian tell you that this is a vertical spar and therefore a mast.",ep:0,g:0,l:150,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11316] = {n:"Retspan Pirate Tooth",t:47,d:"Even the best Frigostian research scientists have failed to explain the usefulness of teeth for a ghost, especially a ghost tied to a mast. Perhaps it uses them to gnaw at the ropes?",ep:0,g:0,l:150,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11317] = {n:"Harpy Pirate Shell",t:111,d:"This shell was stolen from a powerless mollusc by a Harpy Pirate. It hasn\'t made the Harpy Pirate any more powerful so far.",ep:0,g:0,l:155,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11318] = {n:"Harpy Pirate Scale",t:59,d:"This shell belongs to what appears to be a former Frigostian-turned-pirate who was transformed into a ghost when he swallowed too much water while swimming. That\'s what happens when you have too much salt in your diet!",ep:0,g:0,l:155,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11319] = {n:"Vigi Pirate Fabric",t:55,d:"If you turn this fabric over, you\'ll find some invaluable advice: \"If you see an enemy, rob him of his treasure, hide it on a desert island and put a cross on a map so you can remember its location. Remember not to hide the map with the treasure\".",ep:0,g:0,l:155,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11320] = {n:"Vigi Pirate Eye",t:109,d:"Vigi Pirates are selected for their excellent visual capacity. They are able to discern a school of tuna during a storm at night with an octopus covering their eyes, guano on their eyelids and the songs of Jon Lemon playing in the background.",ep:0,g:0,l:155,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11321] = {n:"Buck Anear Hair",t:54,d:"Also known as \"Buck Lightyear\", \"Buck Aroo\", \"Buck Adoaboutnothing\" or \"Buck Off\", this pirate has sailed every sea known to man and beast. The tides have decided that he should end his days on the black sand beaches of the Cradle of Alma.",ep:0,g:0,l:165,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11322] = {n:"Buck Anear Scapula",t:47,d:"Broken twice by cannon balls, three times from rolling in the sea spray, and four times having slipped on dried guano, this bone made a wealthy man of the ship\'s doctor, until he was finally thrown to the sharks for dark tales of gambling, women, alcohol, insubordination, provocations to a duel, treasure theft, scuttling and mutiny. A succession of little things which eventually led to his downfall. You do not mess with Buck Anear.",ep:0,g:0,l:165,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11323] = {n:"Atomystique Stone",t:51,d:"This stone was levitating around an Atomystique until you tried to avoid it, or levitate yourself - you don\'t know exactly what happened, but now you\'ve got a headache and you\'re covered in steaming mud.",ep:0,g:0,l:170,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11324] = {n:"Atomystique Tephra",t:51,d:"This piece of lava was ejected at high speed from an unexpected orifice of an Atomystique that you desperately tried to finish off with a blows from a rusty rake. You were lucky not to be in its way when it went crashing into the arse of a local tourist.",ep:0,g:0,l:170,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11325] = {n:"Solfatare Residue",t:51,d:"How can a vaporous creature give rise to solid waste? This question was first asked 74 years ago during the famous Frigostian contest for the Promotion of Young Graduate Geologists. No participant was admitted that year and the issue still remains one of the Island of Frigost\'s most terrifying mysteries.",ep:0,g:0,l:165,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11326] = {n:"Solfatare Ulna",t:47,d:"This steaming bone changes shape according to the mood of the Solfatare - a beast renowned for its terribly foul moods.",ep:0,g:0,l:165,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11327] = {n:"Steam Crackler Heart",t:51,d:"This stone heart fills with steam when the Steam Crackler meets a partner. This peculiarity allows you to quickly determine if you\'ve killed a single Steam Crackler, you just need to see if its heart floats.",ep:0,g:0,l:175,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11328] = {n:"Steam Crackler Egg",t:105,d:"Steam Cracklers are comparable to Cracklers made from steam that have decided to do battle with anything that does not resemble them in any way, or that they can just about make out through the steam. Surprisingly, they lays eggs filled with steam.",ep:0,g:0,l:175,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11329] = {n:"Fumaroller Stone",t:51,d:"The Fumaroller was waving this huge stone at the end of what appeared to be its tail. He had hoped to intimidate you, until you found his weak point. Unfortunately you failed to memorise it, as your head is full of cotton wool.",ep:0,g:0,l:170,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11330] = {n:"Fumaroller Artefact",t:50,d:"This vaporous artefact smells like rotten eggs mixed with guanocamole. The mere mention of this mixture makes you hungry.",ep:0,g:0,l:170,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11331] = {n:"Mofette Stone",t:51,d:"The mofette takes its name directly from a geological feature that is quite common in the Tears of Ouronigride. This stone resembles one of its organs, a kidney perhaps.",ep:0,g:0,l:175,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11332] = {n:"Mofette Tuff",t:51,d:"Behind this strange name hides a rock with a vascular structure. But you can just be happy likening it to a piece of the giant mofette you just savagely cut in two.",ep:0,g:0,l:175,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11333] = {n:"Magmarmiton Slag",t:51,d:"Even the Magmarmition itself thinks this is junk. Just don\'t put it in your pockets, especially those that aren\'t fireproof.",ep:0,g:0,l:185,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11334] = {n:"Magmarmiton Vertebra",t:47,d:"This vertebra contains bone marrow that has already been cooked and is ready to be consumed. What you are holding in your hands is the precursor to an entire line of microwave ready meals.",ep:0,g:0,l:185,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11335] = {n:"Maho Snowfoux Paw",t:103,d:"After having taken blows from it several times to your face, you finally have the right to keep it in your bag as a lucky charm.",ep:0,g:0,l:185,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11336] = {n:"Maho Snowfoux Ear",t:106,d:"We don\'t know how the Snowfouxes arrived on Frigost, but we know that their distant cousins come from Pandala. This information helps you to better understand the origins of the frozen Pandrista residue you slept in last night.",ep:0,g:0,l:185,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11337] = {n:"Soryo Snowfoux Leather",t:56,d:"This leather is thick enough to allow the Soryo Snowfoux to withstand low, low temperatures and go sledging on his arse without hurting himself, which makes you particularly jealous.",ep:0,g:0,l:190,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11338] = {n:"Soryo Snowfoux Wool",t:57,d:"Long used for stuffing the underwear of complex-ridden Frigostians, this wool is now known to give spots to anyone who strokes it. You have now found an excellent excuse to justify your pestilent pimples.",ep:0,g:0,l:190,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11339] = {n:"Yokai Snowfoux Wool",t:57,d:"It\'s difficult to find anything more stupid than the offspring of a Yokai Snowfoux, yet some parents seem to have succeeded... You\'re looking for a link with this Snowfoux Wool, but you can\'t see any, even squinting and shaking your fists.",ep:0,g:0,l:195,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11340] = {n:"Yokai Snowfoux Skull",t:47,d:"The braincase of the Yokai Snowfoux has just about enough room to hold an evaporated snowflake. But as stupidity is frightening, all Frigostians are terrorised by this creature, even though it\'s barely able to put one paw in front of the other.",ep:0,g:0,l:195,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11341] = {n:"Tengu Snowfoux Wool",t:57,d:"Ripped straight from the body of the Tengu Snowfoux, this wool is particularly warm, and will strengthen your virility if your chest wig is a little sparse.",ep:0,g:0,l:205,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
I.u[11342] = {n:"Tengu Snowfoux Leather",t:56,d:"The completely waterproof leather was used by Frigostians to craft supple, smooth, soft containers to put things in. Some of them even claimed they didn\'t need to use the containers, as they were happily married.",ep:0,g:0,l:205,wd:false,fm:true,w:10,an:0,p:10};
